  "text": "However, in studies when assessing HRV, anxiety and depressive symptoms are mostly associated with increase in HR and corresponding decrease in HRV [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This is even more apparent in anxiety disorders [CITATION_3] and major depressive disorder [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Therefore, there are strong discrepancies between HRV findings in highly anxious and allergic people, although important links between both groups were described.",
